      "content": "A robust, well-defended line of argument centers on national sovereignty and the rule of law. Stricter enforcement is not about hostility; it is a necessary function of any functioning nation-state to control its borders and manage its population legally. Furthermore, increased funding directly addresses transnational criminal organizations and human trafficking, which exploit porous borders for illicit activities that threaten domestic security.",
