      "content": "Thanks, that helps a lot. They're also anticipating that the opposition is going to hit them with arguments about the moral obligation to help migrants or the idea that strict enforcement is inherently inhumane. To keep their arguments from looking weak, could you help them frame a rebuttal to those specific moral/humanitarian critiques? How can they argue that security and enforcement are actually the more ethical or practical path forward?",
